1
00:00:01,161 --> 00:00:26,426
Okay, we can begin.

2
00:00:32,801 --> 00:00:59,350
Sangam Pujeyi Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambhudassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambhudassa

3
00:01:00,341 --> 00:01:24,290
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambuddhasa Bodhansaranam Gacchami Damansaranam Gacchami Sangamsaranam Gacchami

4
00:01:25,046 --> 00:01:51,611
Tuthi Ampi Bodham Saranam Gacchami Tuthi Ampi Dhammam Saranam Gacchami Tuthi Ampi Sangam Saranam Gacchami Tatthi Ampi Bodham Saranam Gacchami

5
00:01:52,283 --> 00:02:21,042
Tatyampi Damang Saranang Gacchami Tatyampi Sandang Saranang Gacchami Panatipata Velamani Sikapadan Samadhi Ami Adhinadana Velamani

6
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:44,852
Sikapadan Samadhi Ami Kamesumi Cacera Velamani Sikapadan Samadhi Ami Musawadda Velamani Sikapadan Samadhi Ami

7
00:02:45,187 --> 00:03:10,193
So we can begin our sitting.

8
00:03:11,033 --> 00:03:14,518
So make sure you are comfortable, feeling comfortable.

9
00:03:18,902 --> 00:03:23,590
Settling on the breath.

10
00:03:23,610 --> 00:03:36,530
We can begin our sitting with these evening contemplations which the Buddha says are there to make us more enthusiastic, to give us some real purpose as to why we're practicing.

11
00:03:39,694 --> 00:03:45,163
So just repeating these phrases to ourselves.

12
00:03:54,205 --> 00:04:21,326
This body is subject to disease This body is of a nature to fall ill This body has not gone beyond sickness This body is subject to aging

13
00:04:26,149 --> 00:04:53,928
This body has not gone beyond aging This body is now in a process of aging This body is subject to death This body has not gone beyond death

14
00:04:58,954 --> 00:05:00,336
This body will die.

15
00:05:00,377 --> 00:05:14,312
There is the unborn, undying, uncreated, uncompounded.

16
00:05:20,358 --> 00:05:21,300
The unconditioned.

17
00:05:26,579 --> 00:05:29,024
True refuge, harbour and home.

18
00:05:34,574 --> 00:05:36,978
Perfect peace and contentment.

19
00:05:43,732 --> 00:05:49,262
Those who are mindful are in the presence, in the vicinity of Nibbana.

20
00:40:56,085 --> 00:41:04,608
So a moment's reflection, just looking back at the time, picking up on something, working with tiredness.

21
00:41:06,833 --> 00:41:07,956
Was it restlessness?

22
00:41:08,036 --> 00:41:09,740
Was some emotional stuff came up?

23
00:41:10,021 --> 00:41:10,903
Wandering mind?

24
00:41:11,485 --> 00:41:12,507
How did you deal with it?

25
00:41:27,996 --> 00:41:33,706
Don't forget, if you thought you were rather skillful, we should congratulate ourselves.

26
00:41:33,786 --> 00:41:37,092
If we thought we could have been more skillful, we should encourage ourselves.

27
00:41:46,949 --> 00:41:52,619
And we can make a resolution, either specific or general or both.

28
00:42:05,239 --> 00:42:33,862
so we can just begin our contemplations always beginning with compassion so again it's a case of turning this goodwill compassion towards ourselves and if we find that difficult just to put our hands over our hearts and just consider some of the things that we've done to ourselves which has caused harm physical mental emotional

29
00:42:36,965 --> 00:42:53,639
something comes up for you and just allow yourself to forgive yourself

30
00:43:02,547 --> 00:43:11,016
Then just turning that compassion towards our own hearts, speaking gently into the heart.

31
00:43:12,697 --> 00:43:15,340
May I be free of physical pain.

32
00:43:20,367 --> 00:43:23,190
May I be free of mental distress.

33
00:43:29,356 --> 00:43:32,519
May I be free of all my sufferings.

34
00:43:53,797 --> 00:43:58,523
We can bring to mind now somebody whom we know is not having a good time one way or the other.

35
00:44:05,853 --> 00:44:10,460
And as you picture them in your mind's eye, just drive your goodwill towards them.

36
00:44:13,423 --> 00:44:15,447
May you be free of physical pain.

37
00:44:20,213 --> 00:44:22,757
May you be free of mental distress.

38
00:44:27,867 --> 00:44:30,907
May you be liberated of all your sufferings.

39
00:44:55,525 --> 00:45:01,070
And we can bring to mind all those at this moment who are sick and or suffering from mental illness.

40
00:45:02,851 --> 00:45:09,438
People in the process of dying and those who have died and left grieving family, relatives and friends.

41
00:45:11,920 --> 00:45:14,862
People going hungry, homeless and destitute.

42
00:45:17,706 --> 00:45:22,409
Those having to deal with severe personal and interpersonal difficulties.

43
00:45:25,900 --> 00:45:31,387
all those caught up in wars and repressive regimes, those being tortured.

44
00:45:34,632 --> 00:45:39,358
And there are those suffering from natural disasters and climate crisis.

45
00:45:43,764 --> 00:45:49,231
All the sentient beings have been cruelly treated and unnecessarily slaughtered.

46
00:45:53,318 --> 00:45:54,760
And all who find life

47
00:45:55,077 --> 00:45:55,797
meaningless.

48
00:46:00,545 --> 00:46:02,588
May you be free of physical pain.

49
00:46:07,516 --> 00:46:09,659
May you be free of mental distress.

50
00:46:16,329 --> 00:46:19,414
May you be liberated of all your sufferings.

51
00:46:42,378 --> 00:47:09,465
we can radiate this goodwill compassion to all beings in all directions may all beings be free of physical pain may all beings be free of mental distress may all beings be liberated of all their sufferings

52
00:47:34,623 --> 00:47:45,034
Bring to mind now some moments during the day when you've experienced love or peace, joy, some level of happiness.

53
00:47:45,235 --> 00:47:46,416
Just bring it to mind.

54
00:47:50,561 --> 00:47:51,702
Be grateful for it.

55
00:48:00,853 --> 00:48:03,297
Then just let's wish ourselves

56
00:48:04,188 --> 00:48:08,958
This joyfulness, again speaking joyfully into the heart.

57
00:48:10,061 --> 00:48:11,364
May I be joyful.

58
00:48:14,791 --> 00:48:16,594
May my joyfulness increase.

59
00:48:22,007 --> 00:48:24,492
May I experience the bliss of Nirvana.

60
00:48:53,985 --> 00:48:58,112
We can bring to mind now somebody whom we know has cause to be joyful.

61
00:49:05,222 --> 00:49:14,135
As you picture them in your mind's eye, drive your goodwill joy towards them.

62
00:49:14,155 --> 00:49:15,396
May you be joyful.

63
00:49:18,922 --> 00:49:20,905
May your joyfulness increase.

64
00:49:25,829 --> 00:49:28,652
May you experience the bliss of nibbana.

65
00:49:49,860 --> 00:49:54,266
And there are people at this moment who are happy and content with their lives.

66
00:49:55,376 --> 00:50:23,342
enjoying the warmth of friendship the support of friendship enjoying the delights of art and nature enjoying the work they do finding it meaningful fruitful and there's also the fruitfulness of those practicing spiritually and there are those who are joyful because they rejoice in the joy of others

67
00:50:28,621 --> 00:50:30,043
May they be joyful.

68
00:50:34,713 --> 00:50:36,516
May their joyfulness increase.

69
00:50:41,726 --> 00:50:44,672
May they experience the bliss of Nirvana.

70
00:51:07,635 --> 00:51:12,043
and radiating this joy to all beings in all directions.

71
00:51:13,344 --> 00:51:15,648
May all beings be joyful.

72
00:51:21,556 --> 00:51:23,300
May their joyfulness increase.

73
00:51:29,728 --> 00:51:35,398
May they experience, may all beings experience the bliss of Nirvana.

74
00:52:06,630 --> 00:52:10,577
I shall read again the discourse on goodwill, Metta.

75
00:52:12,599 --> 00:52:17,686
If you are wise and want to reach the state of peace, you should behave like this.

76
00:52:19,028 --> 00:52:23,195
You should be upright, responsible, gentle and humble.

77
00:52:23,235 --> 00:52:28,503
You should be easily contented and need only a few things.

78
00:52:30,264 --> 00:52:32,148
You should not always be busy.

79
00:52:32,188 --> 00:52:35,693
You should have the right sort of work.

80
00:52:37,327 --> 00:52:41,612
Your senses should be guarded, and you should be modest.

81
00:52:43,394 --> 00:52:52,648
You should not be exclusively attached to only a few people, and you should not do the slightest thing that a wise person would blame you for.

82
00:52:54,791 --> 00:53:07,148
You should always be thinking, may all beings be happy, whatever living beings they are, be they weak or small, big or small, large or slender,

83
00:53:07,550 --> 00:53:14,539
living nearby or far away, those who've already been born and those who have yet to be born.

84
00:53:15,320 --> 00:53:18,204
May all beings, without exception, be happy.

85
00:53:20,407 --> 00:53:26,114
You should not tell lies to each other and do not think anyone anywhere is of no value.

86
00:53:27,697 --> 00:53:31,101
Do not wish harm to anyone, not even when you're angry.

87
00:53:32,523 --> 00:53:37,269
Just as a mother would protect her only child, so you should let that

88
00:53:37,603 --> 00:54:04,032
warmth of your heart go out to all beings let your thoughts of love go through the whole world above and below without any fear with no ill will and no hatred whether you are standing walking sitting or lying down so long as you are awake you should develop this mindfulness this they say is the noblest way to live

89
00:54:05,244 --> 00:54:21,262
And if you do not fall into unskillful ways, but live well and develop insight and are no longer attached to all the desires of the senses, then truly you'll never need to be reborn into this world again.

90
00:54:21,282 --> 00:54:24,365
So I'll chant the discourse.

91
00:54:25,047 --> 00:54:34,898
And if you wish, those of you who know it, of course, can chant with me, but you can also send out these blessings, the normal,

92
00:54:35,197 --> 00:54:39,264
Neta blessings, may you be safe, well and happy.

93
00:54:39,585 --> 00:54:41,208
May you be safe, well and happy.

94
00:54:42,110 --> 00:54:45,817
May you live contented in harmony with the world.

95
00:54:48,802 --> 00:54:57,358
Karaniyangatakusalena, yantang santang padangabhisameca.

96
00:54:58,047 --> 00:55:24,510
Sākhojūcā, Suhujūcā, Suvācchocā, Samuduvaṇāttimāni, Sāntu Sākhocā, Subhārocā, Apākīcocā, Salāhu Kāvuti, Sāntindriyocā, Nīpācocā, Apāgabokuleśu, Anānugīdo,

97
00:55:25,434 --> 00:55:55,222
Nājāgudāṃ samācāre kañcī Yena viṇyūpāre upavadayam Sukhino vākemi nohantu Sābe satabhāvantu sukhi tātā Ye keci pāna bhūtati Tassa vāta vārava ānā vāse sā Dīgā vā ye mahānta vā

98
00:55:55,523 --> 00:55:59,889
Ajima rasa ka nukatula.

99
00:55:59,909 --> 00:56:07,239
Dita wa ye wa adita ye chadure wa santia widure.

100
00:56:08,121 --> 00:56:15,351
Buta wa sambhawesi wa sabhe satabhavan tusukita ta.

101
00:56:16,431 --> 00:56:23,521
Naparo parang niku beta nati manyata kata chilenkenche.

102
00:56:24,835 --> 00:56:52,817
Vyārosāṇā pāttigāsāṇyā nañyāmaṇyāsā dukhaṁ gīcēyāṁ mātāyatā niyāṁ pūtāṁ āyuṣāika pūtāṁ gāṇḍurāke evaṁ pīsābhābhūteṣu mānasāmbhāvāyeyāparīmanāṁ mētencāsābhālokāsmiṁ

103
00:56:52,965 --> 00:57:22,786
Manasambhava Yaya Parimalam Udanga Docha Thiriyanca Asampatanga Verangasapatam Titancharan Nisinova Sayanova Yavadasa Vigatamido Eitan Sathingaditya Brahmangetang Viharangitamahu

104
00:57:23,628 --> 00:57:45,072
dīṭṭhīṁ ca anupāgama-sīla-vātāsānena-sampāṇo kāme suvi-naya-gṛtā na hi cātu-gabhasya-pūṇāre tīṭhī May all beings be happy.

105
00:57:46,092 --> 00:57:51,559
sabhe sakta-sukhita-haṇṭhu

106
00:57:52,231 --> 00:58:08,987
Very good.

107
00:58:09,047 --> 00:58:16,074
Thank you very much.

108
00:58:16,655 --> 00:58:20,418
You might be interested to know that 64 of us were there.

109
00:58:20,498 --> 00:58:22,119
Well, with me, that's 65, isn't it?

110
00:58:22,572 --> 00:58:24,394
practicing meditation together.

111
00:58:24,414 --> 00:58:25,376
How wonderful is that?

112
00:58:26,239 --> 00:58:31,989
So I don't forget from now until you fall asleep is also part of your practice, our practice, don't forget myself.

113
00:58:32,951 --> 00:58:36,878
And it's good to put something beautiful in the mind so you sleep more peacefully.

114
00:58:37,398 --> 00:58:47,195
If it's the meta, remember, make it very simple, just a blessing to yourself, to somebody you have little problems with, and to all beings.

115
00:58:47,480 --> 00:58:58,599
and you can also just put the attention on the breath, but not to investigate, that might wake you up, but just to feel this gentle waving motion wafting you into deep sleep.

116
00:58:59,601 --> 00:59:01,405
May you have a peaceful night.

